    <div class="modal-content">
      <h4>Rules of JS Catchphrase</h4>
      <ol>
        <li>You cannot say the word or any part of the word!</li>
        <li>You cannot use rhyming to get people to guess the word!</li>
        <li>You cannot use spelling to get people to guess the word!</li>
      </ol>
      <div>
        <h5>For example, say you have the phrase <em>baseball bat</em></h5>
        <p><span class="red">NO!</span> "The sport where you run to different bases"</p>
        <p><span class="red">NO!</span> "It rhymes with face call rat"</p>
        <p><span class="red">NO!</span> "Starts with a 'B'"</p>
        <p><span class="green">YES</span> "It's used in America's favorite pasttime"</p>
      </div>
    </div>
